                                        Ruth a day ago edited

                                        Potential plays with the current Doge trend which has potential in my opinion.

                                        They have a presence on Telegram and Twitter. The numbers in channels are growing repaid and do not seem botted. Admins are hyped and have the willingness to answer questions.
                                        They charge 15% tax on each transaction. 5% of which will be added to the LP, and the other 10% redistribute to the holders as BTCB. A reasonable tax rate and novel reward system similar to "Dogeback" which is still doing good.
                                        70% BNB collected from presale contributed to LP which is Good. Could be more, but a reasonable percentage. Additionally, the LP will be locked until 2022.
                                        They did not set a high hard cap. Lower change in buying pressure on launching. (High hard cap=Dumping risks). And each wallet contribution is only 1.5 with a whitelisted system, meaning unlike anyone can be a whale through this presale.
                                        Again, there is no big differences between private sale, presale and listing price. So the buying pressure could be low.
                                        Private: 32,000,000 DRDOGE / 1 BNB
                                        Presale: 30,000,000 DRDOGE / 1 BNB
                                        Listing: 30,000,000 DRDOGE / 1 BNB
                                        At the time of review, there is no further info about their website or details tokenomics, they claim they want to release as perfect version. If true, the team seems dedicated to their project, because I know it only takes few hours to copy/paste others which they did not do.
